Linux
=====

Requirements:
   * Linux distribution with glibc 2.3 or later
   * Qt 5.0.0 or later
   * CMake 3.14 or later
   * GCC C++ compiler, other C++ compilers may work too
   * PATH must contain qmake and g++

Requirements provided in the tools archive:
   * rsync 3.1.2, unpatched
   * getfacl/setfacl 2.2.53, unpatched
   * openssh 8.2p1, unpatched
   * putty 0.74, unpatched
   * script (from util-linux) 2.35.2, unpatched


Mac OS X
========

Requirements:
   * Mac OS X 10.3.9 or later
   * Qt 5.0.0 or later
   * CMake 3.14 or later
   * XCode 2.0 or later
   * PATH must contain qmake and g++

Requirements provided in the tools archive:
   * rsync 2.6.9, unpatched
   * openssh 4.7, unpatched
   * putty 0.60, patched


Windows
=======

Requirements:
   * Windows 2000 or later
   * QT 5.0.0 or later
   * CMake 3.14 or later
   * MinGW 3.4.2 or later
   * PATH must contain qmake and MinGW bin directory

Requirements provided in the tools archive:
   * rsync 3.1.2, unpatched
   * openssh 8.2p1, unpatched
   * putty 0.74, unpatched
   * SetACL 2.0.3.0, patched


All platforms
=============

Compilation:
   * Download a tools archive with precompiled tool binaries for your platform and sepiola version
     from http://sepiola.sourceforge.net/.
     A description how to compile the tools yourself will be added later.
   * Extract the archive in the top level sepiola source directory.
   * Create a subdirectory named "build" in the top level sepiola source directory.
   * Change into the newly created directory.
   * Execute "cmake .."
   * Execute "make"
   
Installation:
   * Execute "make install" in the top level sepiola source directory.
